headline: 1 Healthcare Stock on Our Buy List and 2 to Brush Off
summary: Personal health and wellness is one of the many secular tailwinds for healthcare companies. Despite the rosy long-term prospects, short-term headwinds such as COVID inventory destocking have harmed the industry’s returns - over the past six months, healthcare stocks have collectively shed 8.4%. This drop is a stark contrast from the S&P 500’s 5.4% gain.
